Defendant Robert T Boyce in court with Attorney Chris Bailey.  William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-SIX (36) months.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for EIGHTEEN (18) months with credit for THREE (3) days time served.  Defendant shall serve EIGHTEEN (18) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The Court STAYED the sentence and orders PROBATION for TWO (2) years.

AS TO COUNT #2:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-SIX (36) months consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for EIGHTEEN (18) months with credit for THREE (3) days time served.  Defendant shall serve EIGHTEEN (18) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The Court STAYED the sentence and ordres PROBATION for TWO (2) years.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Seek and maintain full time employment;
 - Pay continuing child support and pay on arrears;
 - TWELVE (12) months HOC time--STAYED--to be used at the Court's and Department's discreation;
 - $1,000 payment towards child support by January 13, 2016.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements AFTER $1,000 payment by the end of extended supervision.  If not paid, will convert to a civil judgment.

The Court set this matter for a review hearing on January 22, 2016 at 8:30am in Br. 30, Judge Conen's court.
